Paranaxia serpulifera
is found in shallow water in northern Australia , often in seagrass beds and generally not on reefs. Despite its large size and prevalence, little research has been carried out on this species. The only nontaxonomic works have focused on the direct development and brooding of the young ( Rathbun 1914 , 1924 ;
Morgan 1987
).
